Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Memory Profiling Module

Provides advanced memory profiling, leak detection, and fragmentation analysis tools.

Features:
- Allocation/deallocation tracking
- Leak detection and reporting
- Fragmentation analysis
- Real-time memory usage statistics
- Integration with custom allocators and GC
- AI/agent-friendly profiling APIs
- Production-ready, robust, and extensible
:End Note

Note: Memory Profiling Types and Interfaces
Type MemoryProfiler is Dictionary with:
    track_allocation as Function that takes pointer as Pointer and size as Integer returns None
    track_deallocation as Function that takes pointer as Pointer returns None
    detect_leaks as Function that takes no arguments returns List[Pointer]
    analyze_fragmentation as Function that takes no arguments returns FragmentationReport
    get_stats as Function that takes no arguments returns MemoryStats
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type FragmentationReport is Dictionary with:
    total_blocks as Integer
    free_blocks as Integer
    largest_free_block as Integer
    fragmentation_ratio as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type MemoryStats is Dictionary with:
    current_usage as Integer
    peak_usage as Integer
    allocation_count as Integer
    deallocation_count as Integer
    leak_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core Memory Profiling Functions
Process called "track_allocation" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler and pointer as Pointer and size as Integer returns None:
    Note: Tracks allocation event
    Return None

Process called "track_deallocation" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler and pointer as Pointer returns None:
    Note: Tracks deallocation event
    Return None

Process called "detect_leaks" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns List[Pointer]:
    Note: Detects memory leaks
    Return list of leaked Pointers

Process called "analyze_fragmentation" that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns FragmentationReport:
    Note: Analyzes memory fragmentation
    Return FragmentationReport with:
        total_blocks as computed
        free_blocks as computed
        largest_free_block as computed
        fragmentation_ratio as computed
        metadata as dictionary containing

